<statement>
<p>Note <m>\displaystyle\frac{{{V}_{{1}}{P}_{{1}}}}{{{T}_{{1}}+{273}}}=\frac{{{V}_{{2}}{P}_{{2}}}}{{{T}_{{2}}+{273}}}</m> with temperature in Celsius.</p>
<p>If <m>\displaystyle{V}_{{1}}={V}_{{2}}={0.250}</m>, <m>\displaystyle{P}_{{1}}={2346}</m>, <m>\displaystyle{T}_{{1}}={14.0}</m>, and <m>\displaystyle{T}_{{2}}={30.0}</m>, what is <m>\displaystyle{P}_{{2}}</m>? <input type="text" style="width:8.2ch" name="qn0" id="qn0" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1" class="text"/></p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>2,480</li></ul></p><p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{{V}_{{1}}{P}_{{1}}}}{{{T}_{{1}}+{273}}}=\frac{{{V}_{{2}}{P}_{{2}}}}{{{T}_{{2}}+{273}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{{0.250}\cdot{2346}}}{{{14.0}+{273}}}=\frac{{{0.250}\cdot{P}_{{2}}}}{{{30.0}+{273}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{{0.250}\cdot{2346}}}{{{14.0}+{273}}}\cdot\frac{{{30.0}+{273}}}{{{0.250}}}={P}_{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2476.787456446}={P}_{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2480}\approx{P}_{{2}}</m>.</p>
</solution>
</myopenmath>